Council Meetings

 

 Ordinary Council Meetings are generally held on the second Tuesday of each month commencing at 6.30pm. All Council meetings are also live streamed here.

Please note that it is strongly recommended that anyone who attends the meeting in person wears a mask whenever social distancing cannot be maintained. 

After each Council meeting, the audio visual recording is checked by the webcasting provider and then indexed to allow convenient direct access to individual agenda items. The indexed recording will be available on the Friday following the meeting. The recording will be retained on Council's website for a period of 12 months after the date of the meeting.

Note:

By using this website or accessing any recording of a Council meeting made available on this website (whether by live stream or otherwise) (Webcast), you acknowledge and agree that:

  1. Camden Council is the owner of all Webcasts, including all copyright subsisting therein;
  2. You must not reproduce or make a copy of, cause to be seen or heard in public, perform or communicate to the public, publish or distribute, or for commercial purposes use or exploit, the whole or a substantial part of any Webcast, or authorise any third party to do so, without the express consent of Camden Council;
  3. Camden Council makes no warranty as to the availability, accuracy, completeness or fitness for any purpose of any Webcast (including the continuity or quality of any live stream of a Webcast), or any other material provided on this website; and
  4. To the extent permitted by law, Camden Council excludes all liability for any loss, damage, cost or expense, howsoever arising (including by negligence), incurred by you or any third party as a result of, or in connection with, whether directly or indirectly, this website, any Webcast, or any other material provided on this website, including the lack of availability of any of the preceding.
